{"nodes":[{"nodeID":"763","text":"The law must be abrogated","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:57"},{"nodeID":"764","text":"California 's law extends the time in which prosecution is allowed","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:57"},{"nodeID":"765","text":"California 's law authorizes prosecutions that the passage of time has previously barred","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:57"},{"nodeID":"766","text":"California 's law was enacted after prior limitations periods for Stogner's alleged offenses had expired","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"767","text":"Such features produce the kind of retroactivity that the Constitution forbids","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"768","text":"If a law is not constitutional it must be abrogated","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"769","text":"the law threatens the kinds of harm that the Clause (of the Constitution) seeks to avoid","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"770","text":"If a law is against a clause of the Constitution the law is forbidden by the Constitution","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"771","text":"the Clause protects liberty by preventing governments from enacting statutes with  manifestly unjust and oppressive   retroactive effects. Calder v. Bull 3 Dall. 386 391","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"772","text":"The law has  manifestly  unjust and oppressive   retroactive effects","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"773","text":"the law falls literally within the categorical descriptions of ex post facto laws that Justice Chase set forth more than 200 years ago in Calder v. Bull","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"775","text":"Ex post fact laws are not constitutional","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"5739","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:36:57","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"5740","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:36:57","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"5741","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:36:57","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"5742","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:36:58","scheme":"EstablishedRule"},{"nodeID":"5743","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:36:58","scheme":"VerbalClassification"},{"nodeID":"5744","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:36:58","scheme":"VerbalClassification"},{"nodeID":"5745","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:36:59","scheme":"VerbalClassification"}],"edges":[{"edgeID":"5369","fromID":"764","toID":"5739","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5370","fromID":"5739","toID":"772","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5371","fromID":"765","toID":"5740","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5372","fromID":"5740","toID":"772","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5373","fromID":"766","toID":"5741","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5374","fromID":"5741","toID":"772","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5375","fromID":"767","toID":"5742","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5376","fromID":"768","toID":"5742","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5377","fromID":"5742","toID":"763","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5378","fromID":"769","toID":"5743","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5379","fromID":"770","toID":"5743","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5380","fromID":"5743","toID":"767","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5381","fromID":"771","toID":"5744","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5382","fromID":"772","toID":"5744","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5383","fromID":"5744","toID":"769","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5384","fromID":"773","toID":"5745","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5385","fromID":"775","toID":"5745","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"5386","fromID":"5745","toID":"767","formEdgeID":null}]}